# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Kronix Frontend Next.js application following the latest official Vercel documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Added**: `@vercel/analytics` v2.0.1 to project dependencies
- **Package Manager**: pnpm (as used by the project)
- **Installation Command**: `pnpm i @vercel/analytics`

### 2. Code Changes
**Modified**: `kronix-frontend/app/layout.tsx`
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the `{children}` element
- Follows the official Next.js App Router integration pattern

### 3. Files Modified
- `kronix-frontend/package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `kronix-frontend/pnpm-lock.yaml` - Updated lock file with new package dependencies
- `kronix-frontend/app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics component integration

## Implementation Details

### Framework Detection
- Project: Next.js 16.2.3 with App Router
- Framework-specific implementation used: `@vercel/analytics/next`

### Documentation Source
Fetched latest instructions from: https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Ensures up-to-date installation procedures
- Framework-specific Next.js App Router instructions followed

### Code Placement
The Analytics component was added to the root layout (`app/layout.tsx`) inside the `<body>` tag as recommended by Vercel documentation. This ensures:
- Analytics tracks all pages in the application
- Seamless integration with Next.js routing
- Automatic visitor and page view tracking

## Verification Steps

### Linting
- Ran ESLint successfully
- No new errors introduced
- Pre-existing warnings unrelated to Analytics changes

### Build Verification
- Build compilation successful
- TypeScript validation passed
- Note: Build encountered a pre-existing error in `/waitlist` page related to missing Supabase configuration (unrelated to Analytics changes)

## Next Steps for Deployment

1. **Enable Analytics in Vercel Dashboard**: Navigate to the project's Analytics section and click "Enable"
2. **Deploy**: Run `vercel deploy` to push changes to production
3. **Verify**: After deployment, check browser's Network tab for analytics requests

## Preserved Code Structure
- All existing imports and functionality maintained
- No changes to existing styling or component structure
- Analytics component added non-invasively at the end of the body tag
